title: Barrhead Leader
description: Between the end of March and beginning of April, Great West Newspapers stopped publishing print editions of 10 community newspapers in Alberta and merged local content into three regional print and digital editions.  Local content that previously appeared in print editions of the Athabasca Advocate, Barrhead Leader and Westlock News is now consolidated into the weekly print publication Town & Country This Week and appears on townandcountrytoday.com.  Local content that previously appeared in print editions of the Bonnyville Nouvelle, Elk Point Review, Lac La Biche Post and St. Paul Journal is now consolidated into the weekly print publication Lakeland This Week and appears on lakelandtoday.ca. Local content that previously appeared in print editions of the Mountain View Albertan, Sundre Round Up and Innisfail Province (which has its own daily newsletter) is now consolidated into the weekly print publication The Albertan and appears on mountainviewtoday.ca. As a result, approximately 30 employees were laid off, representing about 15 per cent of the workforce. These layoffs include employees in sales, administration and 7 in news (proofreading, photographers, sports).

title: Mountain View Gazette
description:
Between the end of March and beginning of April, Great West Newspapers stopped publishing print editions of 10 community newspapers in Alberta and merged local content into three regional print and digital editions. Local content that previously appeared in print editions of the Athabasca Advocate, Barrhead Leader and Westlock News is now consolidated into the weekly print publication Town & Country This Week and appears on townandcountrytoday.com. Local content that previously appeared in print editions of the Bonnyville Nouvelle, Elk Point Review, Lac La Biche Post and St. Paul Journal is now consolidated into the weekly print publication Lakeland This Week and appears on lakelandtoday.ca. Local content that previously appeared in print editions of the Mountain View Albertan, Sundre Round Up and Innisfail Province (which has its own daily newsletter) is now consolidated into the weekly print publication The Albertan and appears on mountainviewtoday.ca. As a result, approximately 30 employees were laid off, representing about 15 per cent of the workforce. These layoffs include employees in sales, administration and 7 in news (proofreading, photographers, sports).
Mountain View Albertan was formed through the merger of the Mountain View Gazette and Olds Albertan. Before that, Mountain View Gazette merged with Didsbury Review and Carstairs Courier in 2016.

title: The North Bay Local
description: The North Bay Local is a mobile app and accompanying website that features local news and community information. The first test app launched on December 18, 2019, and the app officially launched as part of Torstar's hyperlocal expansion strategy with the company's announcement on March 4, 2020. Torstar Local launched 10 of these community engagement hubs in 2020.

title: The Discourse Cowichan Valley

title: The Wilmot Post
description: The Wilmot Post, a weekly community newspaper in Tavistock, published its first issue on October 8, 2020. The newspaper serves the New Hamburg, Baden, New Dundee, Haysville, Mannheim, St. Agatha, Petersburg, Philipsburg, and Punkeydoodle's Corner communities in Ontario.

title: The Woodstock Local
description: The Woodstock Local is a mobile app and accompanying website that features local news and community information. It launched on September 10, 2020, as part of Torstar's hyperlocal expansion strategy. Torstar Local launched 10 of these community engagement hubs in 2020.

title: West Carleton Online
description: This subscription-funded online news site launched July 3, 2018. It covers Ottawaâ€™s Ward 5, a rural area on the cityâ€™s west end. The independently owned site launched six months after PostMedia closed the West Carleton Review newspaper.

title: TVO Eastern Ontario Hub
description: TVO launched the Ontario Hubs program on September 6, 2017, to cover regional news stories across Ontario. The Eastern Hub was added in January, 2018, and is based in Kingston. The Hub reports local news for the Eastern Ontario region. TVO broadcasts Ontario Hubs video reporting throughout the week and articles are posted on their website.

title: TVO Northeastern Ontario Hub
description: TVO launched the Ontario Hubs program on September 6, 2017, to cover regional news stories across Ontario. The Northeastern Hub was added in January, 2018, and is based in Sudbury. The Hub reports local news for the Northeastern Ontario region. TVO broadcasts Ontario Hubs video reporting throughout the week and articles are posted on their website.

title: TVO Northwestern Ontario Hub
description: TVO launched the Ontario Hubs program on September 6, 2017, to cover regional news stories across Ontario. The Northwestern Hub is based in Thunder Bay and reports local news for the Northwestern Ontario region. TVO broadcasts Ontario Hubs video reporting throughout the week and articles are posted on their website.

title: TVO Southwestern Ontario Hub
description: TVO launched the Ontario Hubs program on September 6, 2017, to cover regional news stories across Ontario. The Southwestern Hub is based in London and reports local news for the Southwestern Ontario region. TVO broadcasts Ontario Hubs video reporting throughout the week and articles are posted on their website.

title: WKND 99.5
description: WKND 99.5, a radio station serving the francophone community in Montreal, launched on June 17, 2020.

title: Hometown News
description: This new independent community news source features both a print newspaper and website. It covers news for Smith Falls, Carlton Place, Perth and surrounding areas in Lanark County.
Community: Lanark County / Smith Falls / Carlton Place / Perth, Ontario

title: Cape Breton Spectator
description: An independent, online, weekly newspaper dedicated to Cape Breton Island in general and the Cape Breton Regional Municipality in particular.
Community: Cape Breton Regional Municipality, Nova Scotia

title: Brockville Newswatch
description: Brockville Newswatch is an online-only, independently owned news organization covering news, opinion, sports and weather in the City of Brockville and the United Counties of Leeds & Grenville.

title: YGK News
description: YGK News is a Kingston news publication. It started out of a CFRC radio show and was founded on a need to discuss issues that other news publications werenâ€™t discussing. It aims to deliver engaging, independent media and journalism to the Kingston community. We will endeavor to build a bridge between the community and student populations. We strive to form a bond between the community and the diverse populations within it. To that end, we will be as inclusive as possible.

title: Bow Valley Crag & Canyon
description: Canmore Leader, owned by Sun Media, merged with the Banff Crag & Canyon to become the Bow Valley Crag & Canyon in June 2013.

title: Beaverlodge West County News & Advertiser
description: In January 14, 2014 the Beaverlodge Advertiser and the Beaverlodge West County News merged to create the Beaverlodge West County News & Advertiser.

title: The Sun
description: Metroland community newspapers The Stayner Sun, established in 1877, and the Wasaga Sun, established in 1994, merged to become The Sun in July 2014.

title: Arnprior Chronicle Guide EMC
description: Metroland purchased Arnprior EMC and merged it with the Arnprior Chronicle Guide to create the Arnprior Chronicle EMC in October 2011.

title: Stittsville News EMC
description: Metroland purchased the Stittsville Richmond EMC and merged it with the Stittsville News to create the Stittsville News EMC in October 2011.

title: West Carleton Review EMC
description: Metroland purchased the West Carleton EMC and merged it with the West Carleton Review to create the West Carleton Review EMC in October 2011.

title: The Standard
description: Skyline Media merged the Uxbridge Standard with the Scugog Standard in January 2013 to create The Standard.

title: Williams Lake Tribune
description: The Black Press-owned paper The Cariboo Adviser, the Williams Lake Tribune and its weekend edition, Tribune Weekend, merged on Sept. 4, 2013. They were replaced by the free community paper, the Williams Lake Tribune, distributed on Wednesdays and the Weekend Advisor, published on Fridays.

title: Carleton Place Almonte Canadian Gazette
description: The Carleton Place Almonte Canadian Gazette was the last paper left standing after a series of mergers that resulted in the demise of the Carleton Place Canadian and the Almonte Gazette in February 2009 and the Carleton Place EMC in 2011.

title: The Lunenburg County Progress Bulletin
description: The Lunenburg County Progress Bulletin was created through the merger of the Bridgewater Bulletin (est. 1887) and Lunenburg Progress Enterprise (est. 1876) in May 2011. The new publication is a locally owned independent newspaper published every Wednesday by Lighthouse Media Group.

title: Wainwright Star/Edge
description: The Wainrwright Star and the Wainwright Edge merged to create the Wainright Star/Edge, effective Nov. 1, 2013. The newly created community paper appears on Fridays.

title: Surrey Now- Leader
description: Black Press launched the Surrey Now-Leader after closing The Surrey Now and The Surrey Leader in April 2017.

title: The Echo Pioneer
description: The Echo-Pioneer is a regional community weekly newspaper serving the municipalities of High Level and Mackenzie County, as well as providing regional news to Rainbow Lake, Paddle Prairie Metis Settlement, Dene Tha, Little Red River Cree, Tallcree and Beaver First Nations. The regional publication came into existence April 1, 2015, after the merger of two newspapers: The Echo, established in 1973, and The Northern Pioneer, established in 1976.

title: Weekend Advisor
description: The Black Press-owned paper The Cariboo Adviser, the Williams Lake Tribune and its weekend edition, Tribune Weekend, merged on Sept. 4, 2013. They were replaced by the Weekend Advisor, published on Fridays, and the free community paper, the Williams Lake Tribune, distributed on Wednesdays.

title: Tri-County Vanguard
description: This weekly community print newspaper (published on Tuesdays) was the result of a merger between The Yarmouth Vanguard, The Digby County Courier and The Shelburne County Coast Guard. It was first published Feb. 2, 2016 and covers news for all three counties.

title: Town & Country This Week
description: Between the end of March and beginning of April, Great West Newspapers stopped publishing print editions of 10 community newspapers in Alberta and merged local content into three regional print and digital editions.  Local content that previously appeared in print editions of the Athabasca Advocate, Barrhead Leader and Westlock News is now consolidated into the weekly print publication Town & Country This Week and appears on townandcountrytoday.com.  Local content that previously appeared in print editions of the Bonnyville Nouvelle, Elk Point Review, Lac La Biche Post and St. Paul Journal is now consolidated into the weekly print publication Lakeland This Week and appears on lakelandtoday.ca. Local content that previously appeared in print editions of the Mountain View Albertan, Sundre Round Up and Innisfail Province (which has its own daily newsletter) is now consolidated into the weekly print publication The Albertan and appears on mountainviewtoday.ca. As a result, approximately 30 employees were laid off, representing about 15 per cent of the workforce. These layoffs include employees in sales, administration and 7 in news (proofreading, photographers, sports).

description: Exeter Times-Advocate and Lakeshore Advance merged to form Exeter Lakeshore Times-Advance. The first issue of the Exeter Lakeshore Times-Advance was published on January 24, 2018. The weekly community newspaper serves the communities of Exeter, Grand Bend, Zurich, Hensall, Lucan, and Kirkton.
Community: Exeter, Grand Bend, Zurich, Hensall, Lucan, and Kirkton, Ontario

title: Langley Advance Times
description: Langley Times and Langley Advance merged at the end of February, 2019, to form the Langley Advance Times. The new outlet published its first issue on March 1, 2019, and publishes a print edition every Wednesday and Friday.

title: Meridian Source
description: Lloydminster Source and Lloydminster Meridian Booster merged to form Meridian Source. The first issue of the weekly community newspaper was published on July 5, 2018.

title: Neepawa Banner & Press
description: Neepawa Banner and Neepawa Press merged to form Neepawa Banner & Press. The first issue of the weekly community newspaper was published on October 6, 2017.

title: South Shore

title: Times-Chronicle

title: Norfolk & Tillsonburg News
description: Postmedia merged Tillsonburg News, Lake Shore Shopper and Delhi News-Record to form Norfolk & Tillsonburg News on July 30, 2020. The free weekly newspaper will serve the Tillsonburg, Norfolk and Haldimand communities.

title: Smoky River Peace River Express
description: Smoky River Express and South Peace News merged to form the weekly print publication Smoky River Peace River Express on September 11, 2019. The community paper covers High Prairie, Smokey River and surrounding regions.
Community: High Prairie, Smokey River and surrounding regions, Alberta

title: The City Voice
description: The City Voice is a weekly community newspaper published on Tuesdays that covers local news for the greater Halifax Regional Municipality. The Dartmouth Tribune, Bedford-Sackville Observer and Halifax Citizen community papers merged to become The City Voice April 30, 2019. The paper was temporarily closed at the start of the pandemic when SaltWire announced on March 24 that all of their weekly publications would be suspended for 12 weeks. The last issue was published on March 24, 2020.

title: The Journal
description: The Journal is a free, weekly print publication produced by the merger of Melfort Journal, Nipawin Journal, and Northeast Sun. The first issue was published on August 2, 2019.
Community: Melfort, Nipawin and surrounding area, Saskatchewan

title: Mile Zero-Banner Post

Community: Grimshaw, Berwyn, MD of Peace, Manning and County of Northern Lights, Alberta

title: Alberta Jewish News

title: East Central Recorder

title: Whitewood & Grenfell Herald Sun
description: The Whitewood Herald and Glenfell & Broadview Sun Express community newspapers merged to form Whitewood & Grenfell Herald Sun. The first issue of the weekly community newspaper was published on August 11, 2017.

title: Canadian Jewish News Montreal Edition
description: Canadian Jewish News relaunched as a news website with a national focus in January, 2021. Canadian Jewish News Montreal Edition, a weekly community newspaper serving the Montreal Jewish community, published its final issue on April 9, 2020. The closure was due to the economic impacts of COVID-19. Canadian Jewish News launched in Toronto in 1960, added a Montreal Edition in 1976, shut down temporarily in June, 2013, and was revived in early 2014.

title: Canadian Jewish News Toronto Edition
description: Canadian Jewish News relaunched as a news website with a national focus in January, 2021. Canadian Jewish News Toronto Edition, a weekly community newspaper serving the Toronto Jewish community, published its final issue on April 9, 2020. The closure was due to the economic impacts of COVID-19. Canadian Jewish News launched in Toronto in 1960, added a Montreal Edition in 1976, shut down temporarily in June, 2013, and was revived in early 2014.

title: Eckville Echo
description: Eckville Echo, a weekly community newspaper in Eckville, AB, published its final print edition on March 26, 2020. It was announced as a temporary change due to COVID-19. On June 2, 2020, the publisher confirmed that it would be permanent. Online local news coverage continues.

title: The Daily Oberserver
description: The Daily Observer, a paid daily newspaper, shifted to only publishing online on July 29, 2018.

title: Grande Prairie Daily Herald-Tribune
description: The Grande Prairie Daily Herald-Tribune daily newspaper shifted fully online on May 1, 2021. The last print edition of the newspaper was published on April 30, 2021. On March 4, 2019, the daily newspaper stopped publishing a Monday edition. The newspaper continued to publish a print edition four days per week (Tuesday through Friday). The newspaper launched in 1913.

title: Napanee Guide
description: The Napanee Guide weekly newspaper serving Napanee, ON, published its final print edition on May 7, 2020. The newspaper continues to publish local news on its website. Postmedia announced the closings of 15 community weekly newspapers in Manitoba and Ontario on April 28, 2020, with Napanee Guide and Paris Star continuing as online news outlets.

title: Paris Star
description: The Paris Star weekly newspaper serving Paris, ON, published its final print edition during the week of May 4, 2020. The newspaper continues to publish local news on its website. Postmedia announced the closings of 15 community weekly newspapers in Manitoba and Ontario on April 28, 2020, with Napanee Guide and Paris Star continuing as online news outlets.
